=========================================
C++ ITERATORS - INTERVIEW NOTES
=========================================

QUICK REVISION
=========================================

Iterator:
---------
Used to traverse elements of a container.

Similar to a pointer.

Example:

vector<int> v = {10,20,30};

auto it = v.begin();

cout << *it;   // 10

=========================================
1. Why Do We Need Iterators?
=========================================

✔ Traverse containers
✔ Work with STL algorithms
✔ Provide a common interface for all containers

Example:

sort(v.begin(), v.end());

find(v.begin(), v.end(), 10);

